		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailTitle" style="text-align:center;">
                            Summary on Grant Application Form</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailValue" style="padding:5px;">
                        <span id="lblAbstract">The project will investigate the design and fabrication of a silicon micromachined catalytic calorimeter for combustible gas detection where the calorimeter forms a Fabry-Perot interferometer. The speculative feature of this project is the utilisation of optical energy both to initiate the catalytic reaction and to determine the heat of reaction. An optical fibre conveys light of two different wavelengths to the micro-calorimeter which is attached to the end of the fibre. One wavelength heats the device while the other monitors the temperature change through changes in the response of the Fabry-Perot cavity due to the gas concentration.</span>
                        </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
